**who —** The Power-Up Row — the row of collectible items along the top of the screen — Super Fireball, Boots, Bombs, Ladder, Boomerang, Clapper, Glasses, Swimming Mask, Wings, Shield, and the K marks (collect 50 for a life)

**what —** the row of collectible items along the top of the screen — Super Fireball, Boots, Bombs, Ladder, Boomerang, Clapper, Glasses, Swimming Mask, Wings, Shield, and the K marks (collect 50 for a life)

**where —** KRN · Karnov — Data East, arcade 1987 / NES 1988  Framework inputs: Karnov; the fire-breathing strongman; the Treasure of Babylon; the power-up row  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** They are the game's whole texture: the signature stock-and-spend row, the cartridge's own system made visible across the top of the play.

**how —** Crystallized from Karnov (Data East): the 1987 arcade and the 1987 Famicom / 1988 NES port.

**◌ the mythos —** They are the game's whole texture: the signature stock-and-spend row, the cartridge's own system made visible across the top of the play. a being of the Babylonian-fantasy world and the breath of fire

